//*                 BC0THOR.PDS.JCL(PDSDIRB)                        *
//* READS THE SYSIN FILE TO OBTAIN NAMES OF PDS'S. EACH PDS IS      *
//* DYNAMICALLY ALLOCATED TO DDNAME INPUT1, OPENED FOR INPUT, AND   *
//* ITS DIRECTORY IS READ. FOR EACH MEMBER A RECORD IS WRITTEN TO   *
//* THE SYSOUT FILE CONTAINING MEMBER NAME IN COL 1-8, A DATASET    *
//* NUMBER IN COLUMNS 24-26, AND THE DSNAME IN COL 28-71.           *
//* SEE PDSDIR FOR A SINGLE LIBRARY PROGRAM.                        *
//* SEE PDSDIRC FOR A FULL ATTRIBUTE REPORT LISTING BY MEMBER       *
//* SEE PDS.JCL(PDSDIRLN) FOR LONG SOURCE DIRECTORY LISTING.        *
//*******************************************************************
